website_summaries.verdict: Great taste and texture in a canned food with a high level of protein, but you'll pay extra.
pros: Uses multiple sources of protein and a high percentage of protein, which allows the dog to feel fuller and helps with weight management
Good source of numerous important vitamins and nutrients
Most dogs like the taste and texture
cons: Canned food costs more than dry food
Some dogs may have GI issues with this food

customer_reviews.title: Dogs love it, and healthier than most other dog foods
customer_reviews.text: Dogs love it, and healthier than most other dog foods. Price is comparable to local stores but having it shipped during the busy holiday season is such a great convenience. The cans arrived without any dents and would recommend this dog food to anyone who has a dog with sensitive skin issues.
customer_reviews.author: Nell

customer_reviews.title: Great dog food!
customer_reviews.text: This is the best canned dog food I have ever used. I’m a retired, Certified Dog Groomer, and used to recommend good dog foods when I had my business. It’s all natural, and does not even smell like dog food. I mix a little in my dog’s high quality kibble, and she loves it.
customer_reviews.author: Laurie Jay

customer_reviews.title: Puppy loves food, but all can even the ones in the middle are dented
customer_reviews.text: My dog loves the food, but like other reviewers have written, the cans are dented. And I don't mean just the ones on the outside of the case, even the ones in the center which should be protected by the other cans are dented. This is kind of poor quality control from this vendor. I know its just dog food, but dented can can get contaminated due to the structural integrity and I don't want my dog to eat rust. This food gets high ratings, my dog loves it, but the condition of the cans leads to this middle of the road review
customer_reviews.author: Honest Reviewer130

customer_reviews.title: He does better on it than any other canned food I've gotten ...
customer_reviews.text: My dog has been on Zignature canned food for a couple of years now. He does better on it than any other canned food I've gotten for him. He likes it and no poop issues, not too loose or too hard, as with some other foods. I'm glad to find it on Amazon and be able to get it quickly.
customer_reviews.author: SW

customer_reviews.title: Perfect Poops
customer_reviews.text: My Toy Poodle and Zuchon eat it with toppers. Only canned food I have found that give them firm stools.
customer_reviews.author: Chris Coburg

customer_reviews.title: My dog loves this!
customer_reviews.text: Had to go grain free with my little Pom with skin allergies. This seems to be working. He loves it! It is pricey but since he is so little I can justify the price. Better than meds.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Good quality. Not sure if they care for
customer_reviews.text: Pups are still getting use to it. They like the wet food ok.. dry they will eat some, just don't gobble it up.
customer_reviews.author: 2Smiths

customer_reviews.title: Great for dogs with allergies
customer_reviews.text: Great for dogs that have developed allergies to chicken and grain! Our dog loves it.
customer_reviews.author: Ted Lea

customer_reviews.title: What could be better?
customer_reviews.text: My Jack Russell loves Zignature and so do I because if she likes it and it is GOOD for her - what could be better!
customer_reviews.author: B. J. Marois

customer_reviews.title: Her health & coat are great.
customer_reviews.text: Added this to puppy’s diet, 1/3 can a day to help fill her up. She’s growing fast & needed a little something more.
customer_reviews.author: Kathleen Martin

customer_reviews.title: Not Recommended
customer_reviews.text: Received package intact but one or more cans were leaky causing terrible rotting odor. Left a feedback to seller with no response. Had to throw away the whole package and wasted money.
customer_reviews.author: PREETMOHINDER B.

customer_reviews.title: great ingredients and my dog loves it
customer_reviews.text: I'm happy with the ingredients and my dogs loves it.
customer_reviews.author: Francesca Mongiello

customer_reviews.title: What is in the food?
customer_reviews.text: I’m disappointed that turkey dog food has lamb in it! My dog is allergic to lamb and the ingredients were not listed on amazon . And I can’t return it!!!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: My Dog Love This
customer_reviews.text: I hope this is as healthy as it claims to be because my Dog absolutely loves this dog food.
customer_reviews.author: Lori-Ann Hamilton

customer_reviews.title: Hard to find.
customer_reviews.text: My dog is a 7 lb. Shih Tzu and thrives on this brand.
customer_reviews.author: Matelasse
